<i>[2018 SAT Exams]</i>

139
00:18:12,223 --> 00:18:13,723
<i>[Hyun Ji's college admission results]</i>

140
00:18:18,758 --> 00:18:19,758
<i>[Wait List Results]</i>

141
00:18:27,287 --> 00:18:28,287
<i>[Hyun Ji]</i>

142
00:18:37,101 --> 00:18:38,101
<i>[Wait List Results]</i>

143
00:19:04,390 --> 00:19:07,510
You see me, don't you?
How dare you ignore me!

144
00:19:09,891 --> 00:19:12,259
Go away!

145
00:19:20,985 --> 00:19:24,023
I don't want any bad luck on
an important day like this.

146
00:19:24,024 --> 00:19:25,977
I said get lost!

147
00:19:30,881 --> 00:19:33,444
Why are there so many
ghosts like that these days?

148
00:19:42,633 --> 00:19:46,923
<i>Please enter the six digits of
your birthday for Myungsung University.</i>

149
00:20:16,322 --> 00:20:17,322
<i>[Hyun Ji]</i>

150
00:20:20,072 --> 00:20:21,643
Hello?

151
00:20:21,644 --> 00:20:23,754
- <i>Bong Pal.</i>
- What happened?

152
00:20:23,755 --> 00:20:26,640
<i>I'm sorry.
I didn't pass the exam.</i>

153
00:20:26,641 --> 00:20:28,922
You didn't get in?

154
00:20:30,534 --> 00:20:33,901
That's okay, you can
just do better next time.

155
00:20:33,902 --> 00:20:36,730
With that score,
you'll pass for sure next time.

156
00:20:36,731 --> 00:20:40,364
Still, I wanted to
go to school with you.

157
00:20:40,365 --> 00:20:42,613
You're graduating this year.

158
00:20:42,614 --> 00:20:45,044
Well, I'll sit this semester out.

159
00:20:46,404 --> 00:20:48,598
Forget it. Don't be ridiculous.

160
00:20:49,602 --> 00:20:51,851
You need to get a job right away.

161
00:20:51,852 --> 00:20:54,863
That way you can start
planning for the future.

162
00:20:54,864 --> 00:20:56,744
That way...

163
00:20:57,840 --> 00:21:00,997
- That way what?
- You know what I'm talking about.

164
00:21:00,998 --> 00:21:03,083
So what is it?

165
00:21:03,084 --> 00:21:05,190
- You really don't know?
- I don't know.

166
00:21:05,191 --> 00:21:08,566
Is that right? Then you're
going to live alone forever.

167
00:21:08,567 --> 00:21:10,393
Why should I live alone?

168
00:21:10,394 --> 00:21:12,587
I'm going to live with you.

169
00:21:12,588 --> 00:21:14,059
<i>After four years.</i>

170
00:21:14,061 --> 00:21:15,480
Why after four years?

171
00:21:15,481 --> 00:21:18,708
By then, I'll have a stable career.

172
00:21:18,709 --> 00:21:22,688
You'll be graduating about
that time, so it's perfect.

173
00:21:22,689 --> 00:21:24,334
<i>What do you think? You like it, right?</i>

174
00:21:25,548 --> 00:21:28,561
Who said I'm going
to live with you, huh?

175
00:21:28,562 --> 00:21:30,336
<i>You're funny.</i>

176
00:21:30,337 --> 00:21:32,880
Ah, when do classes start?

177
00:21:33,975 --> 00:21:36,960
- March fifth.
- That's coming up soon.

178
00:21:36,961 --> 00:21:38,814
You're going to be busy.

179
00:21:40,817 --> 00:21:43,588
How am I going to wait another year?

180
00:21:43,590 --> 00:21:45,431
It'll pass soon enough.

181
00:22:13,928 --> 00:22:16,831
- Come join our club!
- Hello!

182
00:22:20,459 --> 00:22:24,250
A price that doesn't honor
the value of the property...

183
00:22:25,355 --> 00:22:27,720
It's not simple like this.

184
00:22:27,721 --> 00:22:29,953
Okay, that's all for class today.

185
00:22:29,954 --> 00:22:36,187
I want you to submit a group report
next week on resource distribution.

186
00:22:36,917 --> 00:22:38,453
Quiet.

187
00:22:39,411 --> 00:22:43,222
Here are the designated groups.
Take a look before you leave.

188
00:22:44,682 --> 00:22:47,780
Good job on your first day of class.

189
00:22:47,781 --> 00:22:49,385
See you next week.

190
00:22:49,386 --> 00:22:52,065
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

191
00:22:57,591 --> 00:22:59,502
Senior Bong Pal.

192
00:22:59,504 --> 00:23:03,200
We're in the same group
and we're counting on you.

193
00:23:05,492 --> 00:23:06,492
<i>[Park Bong Pal]</i>

194
00:23:08,843 --> 00:23:11,219
- Okay, let's do our best.
- Okay!

195
00:23:11,220 --> 00:23:13,036
See you next week.

196
00:23:18,487 --> 00:23:21,055
Hey, Bong Pal!
Bong Pal, Bong Pal, Bong Pal!

197
00:23:21,818 --> 00:23:23,768
- Senior.
- We're in trouble.

198
00:23:23,769 --> 00:23:25,903
- What's going on?
- We're in trouble. What do we do?

199
00:23:25,904 --> 00:23:27,370
What's wrong?

200
00:23:27,977 --> 00:23:29,968
You'll know once you get there.

201
00:23:29,969 --> 00:23:31,042
Senior! Senior!

202
00:23:31,823 --> 00:23:33,516
<i>[Notice of Compliance]</i>

203
00:23:44,048 --> 00:23:50,362
In Rang is gone, Seo Yeon is gone,
and not a single freshman is willing...

204
00:23:51,441 --> 00:23:53,418
What are we supposed to do now?

205
00:23:53,419 --> 00:23:56,839
Our club is in danger
of being shut down again.

206
00:23:56,840 --> 00:23:59,889
- That's too bad, I guess.
- That's... "That's too bad, I guess."

207
00:23:59,890 --> 00:24:02,035
We're in a crisis right now.

208
00:24:02,036 --> 00:24:04,183
As co-president,
how can you be so nonchalant?

209
00:24:04,184 --> 00:24:05,725
Who is co-president?

210
00:24:06,213 --> 00:24:08,061
- Me?
- Then who else would it be?

211
00:24:08,062 --> 00:24:11,079
It's just the two of us.
Who else would it be?

212
00:24:11,081 --> 00:24:13,367
You have to be the next
president once I graduate!

213
00:24:13,369 --> 00:24:15,388
I'm not really interested.

214
00:24:15,389 --> 00:24:19,028
So... the tradition and
history we're so proud of...

215
00:24:19,029 --> 00:24:24,642
Are you saying you want to get
rid of our Blood Sausage Soup club?

216
00:24:24,643 --> 00:24:26,199
I have to go to class. See you.

217
00:24:26,200 --> 00:24:27,880
Don't go.

218
00:24:28,527 --> 00:24:29,968
Be strong.

219
00:24:29,969 --> 00:24:33,461
Don't go, Bong Pal. Don't go, Bong Pal.
Bong Pal, Bong Pal, Bong Pal!

220
00:24:34,411 --> 00:24:36,088
Bong Pal!

221
00:24:38,683 --> 00:24:40,927
You selfish bastard.

222
00:24:43,629 --> 00:24:45,258
<i>[In Rang]</i>

223
00:24:47,847 --> 00:24:49,467
Hello?

224
00:24:49,468 --> 00:24:53,354
<i>What time is it? Come quickly if
class is over! What are you doing? Huh?</i>

225
00:24:53,355 --> 00:24:55,451
I'll be right there. Don't get annoyed.

226
00:24:55,452 --> 00:24:58,507
- <i>Hurry up! Class is over!</i>
- Stop nagging.

227
00:24:58,508 --> 00:25:00,534
- <i>Move it!</i>
- I'm coming!

228
00:25:06,826 --> 00:25:10,024
Exorcism is about getting rid of
ghosts, evil spirits, and monsters

229
00:25:10,025 --> 00:25:11,776
that inhabit humans and places.

230
00:25:11,777 --> 00:25:15,439
It is a scary and dirty job.

231
00:25:15,440 --> 00:25:20,285
Shamans, monks, and the spiritually
blessed have been exorcising for years.

232
00:25:20,286 --> 00:25:24,459
In 2018, Blood Sausage Soup has
joined hands with these people...

233
00:25:24,460 --> 00:25:26,064
Excuse me.

234
00:25:27,486 --> 00:25:29,335
Is there anything you're curious about?

235
00:25:30,677 --> 00:25:34,275
I don't know where and what went wrong

236
00:25:34,276 --> 00:25:38,091
- but I need to ask now.
- Yes, please go ahead.

237
00:25:39,692 --> 00:25:42,146
Isn't this
a blood sausage soup restaurant?

238
00:25:42,148 --> 00:25:44,074
I wanted a bowl of it to go.

239
00:25:44,075 --> 00:25:46,489
- You want it to go?
- It's a service everyone offers lately.

240
00:25:46,490 --> 00:25:48,717
No... it's not.

241
00:25:50,353 --> 00:25:52,806
- Yes, we're...
- Gosh, I'm so sorry!

242
00:25:52,807 --> 00:25:55,083
- I came to a ghost-catching business.
- Yes, I'm sorry.

243
00:25:55,084 --> 00:25:57,364
- I'm sorry.
- No, I'm sorry.

244
00:25:57,365 --> 00:25:59,611
- I'm truly sorry.
- Not at all. I'm sorry.

245
00:25:59,612 --> 00:26:02,451
- I should've been more clear. Goodbye.
- Yes, goodbye.

246
00:26:02,452 --> 00:26:05,313
- Goodbye.
- This is not a restaurant.

247
00:26:07,950 --> 00:26:09,619
Did you get work for us? Huh?

248
00:26:09,620 --> 00:26:14,832
Our name is Blood Sausage Soup,
so he came to eat.

249
00:26:14,833 --> 00:26:16,902
What time is it right now?

250
00:26:16,903 --> 00:26:19,882
Why are you MIA lately?
Did you pass out the flyers?

251
00:26:19,883 --> 00:26:21,963
I did. I did pass the flyers out

252
00:26:21,965 --> 00:26:24,785
but I think we need to
hire a part-time employee.

253
00:26:24,786 --> 00:26:26,815
It's kind of hard doing
this all by myself.

254
00:26:26,816 --> 00:26:28,245
A part-time employee?

255
00:26:28,246 --> 00:26:31,355
How can that just easily
come out of your mouth?

256
00:26:32,062 --> 00:26:35,169
We haven't had a single job
since we opened up our business!

257
00:26:35,170 --> 00:26:37,302
And wait a minute.

258
00:26:37,303 --> 00:26:39,161
Look at this.

259
00:26:40,031 --> 00:26:43,673
I see that you ate a special
variety meat set yesterday.

260
00:26:43,674 --> 00:26:45,817
I told you to cut off
meals at 5,500 won!

261
00:26:45,818 --> 00:26:47,191
5,500 won meals are hard to find.

262
00:26:47,192 --> 00:26:49,237
I just ate one for 5,000 won!

263
00:26:49,238 --> 00:26:51,946
We will never be able to pay
my grandma back at this rate!

264
00:26:51,947 --> 00:26:55,461
I got this investment because I believed
in you! You said it would be a hit!

265
00:26:55,462 --> 00:26:57,093
You said we could pay
it all back in a month.

266
00:26:57,094 --> 00:27:02,572
The thing is, if you look at the way
the economy is doing these days...

267
00:27:06,319 --> 00:27:08,207
What about new freshman recruits?

268
00:27:09,000 --> 00:27:10,748
We're still...

269
00:27:11,895 --> 00:27:14,102
Still?

270
00:27:15,594 --> 00:27:18,768
We received a grant from the school
and we still have no new members?

271
00:27:18,769 --> 00:27:23,545
We're going to jail
if the school finds out.

272
00:27:23,546 --> 00:27:27,036
Look, I'm doing my very best.

273
00:27:31,693 --> 00:27:33,506
- Let's clean this place up.
- Huh?

274
00:27:33,507 --> 00:27:37,660
Let's do some cleaning. Let's clean
the windows and dust the office.

275
00:27:37,661 --> 00:27:39,972
My head hurts,
so I'm going to rest a bit.

276
00:27:39,973 --> 00:27:43,129
- Clean?
- Go ahead and start.

277
00:27:44,188 --> 00:27:46,324
You want me to clean?

278
00:27:46,325 --> 00:27:48,295
I'm the CEO.

279
00:27:48,296 --> 00:27:51,305
I have to do all the dirty work just
because you got the investment money.

280
00:27:51,306 --> 00:27:54,122
Yeah, I don't blame you
for rubbing it in my face.

281
00:27:54,123 --> 00:27:55,805
- Do we have coffee?
- Yes, we do.

282
00:27:55,806 --> 00:27:59,266
- How do you want it?
- Just black.

283
00:28:00,247 --> 00:28:03,722
- Goodness, it's been a long time.
- Yes, Monk Myung Chul.

284
00:28:04,844 --> 00:28:07,980
I hope I'm not late.

285
00:28:07,981 --> 00:28:11,523
The thing is, I've been
trying to get a hold of you

286
00:28:11,524 --> 00:28:12,964
and you're not answering your phone.

287
00:28:14,777 --> 00:28:16,944
Is there something going on?

288
00:28:16,946 --> 00:28:22,386
The shamaness has told us that your
prayers and energy have no effect at all.

289
00:28:22,388 --> 00:28:26,355
Which shamaness is going around
saying such nonsense about me?

290
00:28:26,356 --> 00:28:29,049
What do you mean nonsense?

291
00:28:45,504 --> 00:28:48,049
Why are you here?

292
00:28:49,463 --> 00:28:54,538
Why can't you cross
over to the afterlife?

293
00:28:55,585 --> 00:28:59,713
Believe. Redeem your sorry soul!

294
00:29:08,613 --> 00:29:11,667
Who is this pitiful-looking man?

295
00:29:11,668 --> 00:29:13,394
Get rid of him.

296
00:29:18,292 --> 00:29:20,065
What is this?

297
00:29:20,066 --> 00:29:21,893
She's from Daeryong Mountain.

298
00:29:21,894 --> 00:29:23,723
She calls herself
the 1,000-year-old virgin shamaness.

299
00:29:23,725 --> 00:29:25,437
A virgin shamaness?

300
00:29:25,438 --> 00:29:28,680
Why are there so many?
She's not a virgin shamaness!

301
00:29:28,681 --> 00:29:30,341
She's just a con artist!

302
00:29:31,139 --> 00:29:35,475
You insolent fool! Leave immediately!

303
00:29:35,476 --> 00:29:39,492
You have no credentials or pedigree!
How dare you con these good people!

304
00:29:39,494 --> 00:29:43,142
How dare you call me a fraud!

305
00:29:43,821 --> 00:29:46,715
I can't believe you dragged this
good-for-nothing monk into the house!

306
00:29:46,716 --> 00:29:50,528
I'm a great and honorable
monk who catches evil spirits!

307
00:29:50,529 --> 00:29:53,986
Leave if you're done! How dare you
impersonate a shamaness, you fake.

308
00:29:53,987 --> 00:29:57,095
Fake? Fake?

309
00:29:58,457 --> 00:30:00,322
- Oh my.
- What's wrong?

310
00:30:06,894 --> 00:30:08,552
What is going on?

311
00:30:08,553 --> 00:30:10,227
Have you lost your mind?

312
00:30:15,171 --> 00:30:17,273
Goodness, attention!

313
00:30:17,803 --> 00:30:19,789
Congratulations on your promotion.

314
00:30:20,344 --> 00:30:22,775
Stop, you're embarrassing me.

315
00:30:23,885 --> 00:30:26,000
Chief.

316
00:30:26,001 --> 00:30:27,777
Chief.

317
00:30:32,218 --> 00:30:34,228
Why did you push her?

318
00:30:34,229 --> 00:30:36,700
I didn't push her.

319
00:30:36,701 --> 00:30:39,594
This woman couldn't control her
anger and she tripped and fell.

320
00:30:39,595 --> 00:30:41,689
She says she's a virgin shamaness.

321
00:30:41,690 --> 00:30:44,969
