I think this woman is a fraud.

322
00:30:47,941 --> 00:30:51,341
Why do you keep hitting me, woman?

323
00:30:52,468 --> 00:30:56,267
Stop her! She's attacking me!

324
00:30:57,097 --> 00:30:59,489
Calm down!

325
00:31:00,834 --> 00:31:03,610
Have we met before?
You look familiar.

326
00:31:03,611 --> 00:31:05,401
- I go to church.
- Hallelujah?

327
00:31:05,402 --> 00:31:06,701
Amen.

328
00:31:07,807 --> 00:31:10,033
Stop her!

329
00:31:12,411 --> 00:31:14,456
- Senior.
- Senior.

330
00:31:14,457 --> 00:31:16,020
Where are you going?

331
00:31:16,021 --> 00:31:18,913
- I'm going home.
- Don't go home.

332
00:31:18,914 --> 00:31:21,555
There's the freshman
welcome party today.

333
00:31:21,556 --> 00:31:22,931
Ah.

334
00:31:22,932 --> 00:31:25,670
- I'm not interested in those events.
- No, you have to go.

335
00:31:25,671 --> 00:31:28,266
You have to be there.

336
00:31:28,267 --> 00:31:30,650
- Please go.
- Let's go together.

337
00:31:30,651 --> 00:31:32,881
Senior, let's go.

338
00:31:33,402 --> 00:31:35,269
Let's go.

339
00:31:36,006 --> 00:31:37,798
Are all the drinks poured?

340
00:31:37,799 --> 00:31:41,106
- Do you all have drinks or not?
- We do!

341
00:31:41,107 --> 00:31:43,694
It's rare to drink with us seniors!

342
00:31:43,696 --> 00:31:46,374
Economy major cheer on
the count of three, got it?

343
00:31:46,375 --> 00:31:48,025
- Yes!
- One, two, three!

344
00:31:48,026 --> 00:31:50,604
Economy major!

345
00:31:54,146 --> 00:31:56,759
There is a really pretty freshman
girl who got admitted this year.

346
00:31:56,760 --> 00:31:59,198
I saw her too. She's totally hot.

347
00:31:59,199 --> 00:32:02,456
Hello, I'm economy major
Kim Ji Eun, class of 2018.

348
00:32:02,457 --> 00:32:04,749
Please take good care of me.

349
00:32:06,261 --> 00:32:10,624
Hello, I'm economy major...

350
00:32:10,625 --> 00:32:13,586
- She's so cute.
- Please take good care of me.

351
00:32:15,414 --> 00:32:18,558
Hello, I'm economy major
Lee Dong Min, class of 2018.

352
00:32:18,559 --> 00:32:22,981
It's my goal to become
the Adam Smith of Korea. Thank you.

353
00:32:25,348 --> 00:32:28,867
Hello, Seniors. I'm economy
major Kim Hyun Ji, class of 2018.

354
00:32:28,869 --> 00:32:30,874
I'd appreciate your guidance.

355
00:32:30,875 --> 00:32:32,619
Hey, she's the one!

356
00:32:34,517 --> 00:32:36,216
- I have a question.
- Yes?

357
00:32:36,217 --> 00:32:38,523
By any chance, do you have a boyfriend?

358
00:32:43,754 --> 00:32:46,296
Yes, he's here.

359
00:32:46,297 --> 00:32:47,855
He's here?

360
00:33:00,201 --> 00:33:02,698
Why did you lie about not passing?

361
00:33:02,699 --> 00:33:06,258
I did it on purpose
so I could surprise you.

362
00:33:06,874 --> 00:33:10,343
I had no idea. I was wondering how
I was going to wait another year.

363
00:33:10,344 --> 00:33:11,869
You said it'll pass soon enough.

364
00:33:11,870 --> 00:33:13,888
I didn't mean it.

365
00:33:15,485 --> 00:33:18,500
But where are you staying?

366
00:33:18,501 --> 00:33:20,590
At my uncle's.
It's close to your place too.

367
00:33:20,591 --> 00:33:22,569
Really? Good.

368
00:33:24,162 --> 00:33:27,109
- Aren't you happy to see me?
- Of course.

369
00:33:28,246 --> 00:33:31,650
From now on, I'm going
to stick to you like glue.

370
00:33:31,651 --> 00:33:34,390
You better be good to me from now on.

371
00:33:34,392 --> 00:33:36,388
- Older sister?
- Of course, I'm older than you.

372
00:33:36,390 --> 00:33:39,008
You're one year younger than me.

373
00:33:39,009 --> 00:33:41,538
Older sister, my butt.

374
00:33:41,540 --> 00:33:44,532
Let's get the nicknames out of the way.

375
00:33:44,533 --> 00:33:47,484
Bong Pal, repeat after me.

376
00:33:47,486 --> 00:33:49,614
Older sister.

377
00:33:50,428 --> 00:33:51,918
No.

378
00:33:51,919 --> 00:33:55,666
You better listen to me.
One more time. "Older sister."

379
00:33:55,667 --> 00:33:59,200
- Forget it.
- Why? Just say it once, okay?

380
00:33:59,201 --> 00:34:00,892
Older sister. Older sister.

381
00:34:00,893 --> 00:34:03,152
- No, I don't want to!
- Say "older sister"!

382
00:34:03,154 --> 00:34:05,100
Just say it this once. Please?

383
00:34:15,337 --> 00:34:18,698
- Now go in.
- Okay.

384
00:34:19,160 --> 00:34:20,908
- Good night.
- Good night.

385
00:34:43,640 --> 00:34:45,685
- What's the matter?
- I just like you so much.

386
00:34:52,582 --> 00:34:54,446
I like you a lot too.

387
00:35:02,263 --> 00:35:05,202
- Go in now.
- All right.

388
00:35:05,203 --> 00:35:07,372
- Sweet dreams.
- You too.

389
00:35:25,828 --> 00:35:27,388
Hi, Monk Myung Chul.

390
00:35:33,118 --> 00:35:34,377
Hello.

391
00:35:35,038 --> 00:35:37,038
Where is Monk Myung Chul?

392
00:35:42,948 --> 00:35:44,457
Bong Pal.

393
00:35:51,488 --> 00:35:53,227
I'm sorry.

394
00:35:55,268 --> 00:35:56,746
Gosh, you're not a kid.

395
00:35:56,747 --> 00:35:58,476
How could you get into a fight, huh?

396
00:35:58,477 --> 00:36:00,827
In my field, there are
business ethics to follow.

397
00:36:00,828 --> 00:36:02,316
That shamaness didn't do it.

398
00:36:02,317 --> 00:36:04,508
That's why I... taught her a lesson.

399
00:36:05,658 --> 00:36:08,828
- Thank you. I will go now.
- Monk Myung Chul.

400
00:36:10,368 --> 00:36:12,718
- Yes?
- Well...

401
00:36:14,067 --> 00:36:15,896
You're not well and all.

402
00:36:15,897 --> 00:36:17,627
Why don't you stop working?

403
00:36:17,837 --> 00:36:20,507
Stop working and stay with me.

404
00:36:20,508 --> 00:36:22,586
- With you?
- Yes.

405
00:36:22,587 --> 00:36:25,308
Your place in the mountain
isn't very comfortable.

406
00:36:25,828 --> 00:36:27,517
I emptied the spare room.

407
00:36:27,518 --> 00:36:30,258
Move in with me. I know it's such
a hassle to commute back and forth.

408
00:36:31,118 --> 00:36:32,456
Bong Pal.

409
00:36:32,457 --> 00:36:36,127
You're the only family member I have now.

410
00:36:36,647 --> 00:36:38,127
Gosh.

411
00:36:45,027 --> 00:36:47,158
You know how to make people cry, huh?

412
00:36:49,297 --> 00:36:51,268
Do you have any sausage at home?

413
00:36:51,607 --> 00:36:55,047
On a day like this, it'll be great
to have soju and sausage.

414
00:36:57,247 --> 00:36:58,868
Let's go.

415
00:37:12,888 --> 00:37:14,468
What's wrong?

416
00:37:27,698 --> 00:37:29,158
Hyun Ji!

417
00:37:29,618 --> 00:37:31,238
Hey, Soo Jin.

418
00:37:31,678 --> 00:37:34,007
Do you have time tonight?

419
00:37:34,008 --> 00:37:35,737
What? What about tonight?

420
00:37:35,738 --> 00:37:37,947
Management department guys
asked three girls out on a blind date.

421
00:37:37,948 --> 00:37:40,357
- Can you please come with us?
- A blind date?

422
00:37:41,758 --> 00:37:44,336
Well, you know I have a boyfriend.

423
00:37:44,337 --> 00:37:47,746
We know that you're going out
with one of our seniors.

424
00:37:47,747 --> 00:37:50,706
Can you keep this from him
and come out with us this once?

425
00:37:50,707 --> 00:37:52,787
We were afraid
the guys would be a disaster.

426
00:37:52,788 --> 00:37:54,517
So we told them we'd bring
the prettiest girl in our department.

427
00:37:54,518 --> 00:37:57,226
They told me that they'd bring
the handsomest boys. Please.

428
00:37:57,227 --> 00:38:00,027
Come on, me the prettiest girl?

429
00:38:00,738 --> 00:38:03,206
If Bong Pal finds out,
he will get really mad.

430
00:38:03,207 --> 00:38:05,007
Once people know you two are going out

431
00:38:05,008 --> 00:38:06,356
you will never be asked
on a blind date.

432
00:38:06,357 --> 00:38:09,667
You got into college and will graduate
without being on a blind date?

433
00:38:12,788 --> 00:38:14,957
Wow, she is really pretty.

434
00:38:15,808 --> 00:38:18,768
With the other two,
she looks even prettier.

435
00:38:20,428 --> 00:38:23,697
Hello, I'm a freshman in
the Management department, Kim Tae Young.

436
00:38:23,698 --> 00:38:25,987
You're as pretty as we've heard.

437
00:38:25,988 --> 00:38:28,217
Really? Thank you.

438
00:38:28,218 --> 00:38:30,927
What is this? Only three boys were
supposed to come meet us.

439
00:38:30,928 --> 00:38:33,847
They all begged me to come along.

440
00:38:33,848 --> 00:38:36,047
We managed to cut many others.

441
00:38:40,377 --> 00:38:41,988
Here.

442
00:38:47,488 --> 00:38:49,877
Thank you.

443
00:38:58,308 --> 00:39:00,357
<i>[My love Bong Bong]</i>

444
00:39:06,497 --> 00:39:09,107
<i>Your call is being redirected...</i>

445
00:39:11,868 --> 00:39:14,718
<i>I'm done with my class.
Where are you?</i>

446
00:39:15,247 --> 00:39:18,137
<i>I'm discussing homework
with my classmates at a café.</i>

447
00:39:18,138 --> 00:39:19,316
<i>I will call you later.</i>

448
00:39:19,317 --> 00:39:21,847
Let's break the ice, shall we?

449
00:39:21,848 --> 00:39:24,308
Can we go around
and introduce ourselves first?

450
00:39:25,508 --> 00:39:27,268
- Sure.
- Me first?

451
00:39:28,937 --> 00:39:30,937
What homework all of a sudden?

452
00:39:34,997 --> 00:39:36,768
I guess I will just go then.

453
00:39:41,777 --> 00:39:44,606
Drink up! Drink up!

454
00:39:44,607 --> 00:39:48,077
Alcohol is coming. Drink up!

455
00:39:48,078 --> 00:39:49,868
It will make you want to dance.

456
00:39:59,698 --> 00:40:04,267
- A knight to the rescue.
- A knight to the rescue.

457
00:40:04,268 --> 00:40:06,757
- I can drink this.
- No way.

458
00:40:06,758 --> 00:40:09,207
- I will drink it.
- Come on.

459
00:40:21,667 --> 00:40:23,258
I'm the knight for you!

460
00:40:35,768 --> 00:40:37,967
<i>[We're on a blind date with girls
from the Management Department.]</i>

461
00:40:37,968 --> 00:40:39,957
<i>[They're the best.]</i>

462
00:40:48,209 --> 00:40:52,237
- Hello, In Rang.
- Hi, Pal. Where are you now?

463
00:40:52,238 --> 00:40:54,396
- I'm at home.
- Are you?

464
00:40:54,397 --> 00:40:57,407
Do you happen to know where Hyun Ji is?

465
00:40:57,408 --> 00:40:58,408
Hyun Ji?

466
00:40:59,377 --> 00:41:01,456
She said she's
at a café doing homework.

467
00:41:01,457 --> 00:41:03,607
Ah, she's doing her homework at a café...

468
00:41:04,598 --> 00:41:09,296
Pal, do you want to take a look
at the video I'm sending now?

469
00:41:09,297 --> 00:41:10,397
Sure.

470
00:41:17,328 --> 00:41:20,037
<i>This is the game that Hyun Ji likes!</i>

471
00:41:20,038 --> 00:41:21,788
<i>Here we go.</i>

472
00:41:40,247 --> 00:41:41,947
You two look like a couple.

473
00:41:41,948 --> 00:41:43,623
- Don't we?
- Let's go for the second round.

474
00:41:43,647 --> 00:41:45,448
Did you two already decide?

475
00:41:48,558 --> 00:41:50,967
- Hyun Ji...
- Yes? What?

476
00:41:50,968 --> 00:41:52,598
Senior Bong Pal.

477
00:41:58,897 --> 00:42:01,837
- By the way, who is this?
- Me?

478
00:42:05,667 --> 00:42:07,397
I'm Hyun Ji's boyfriend.

479
00:42:17,828 --> 00:42:20,276
Bong Pal, are you really mad?

480
00:42:20,277 --> 00:42:23,717
I always wanted to
go on a blind date at college.

481
00:42:23,718 --> 00:42:25,718
Can you let it go this once, please?

482
00:42:26,788 --> 00:42:28,347
When you have a boyfriend... what?

483
00:42:28,348 --> 00:42:29,916
You went on a blind date
and you want me to let it go?

484
00:42:29,917 --> 00:42:32,413
- I told them that I had a boyfriend.
- What?

485
00:42:32,437 --> 00:42:35,827
When we were introducing ourselves,
I told them I had a boyfriend.

486
00:42:35,828 --> 00:42:38,368
If you don't trust me,
go ask them.

487
00:42:38,817 --> 00:42:42,237
I just went there to feel
the craziness of college life.

488
00:42:42,238 --> 00:42:44,237
- You got into college for this, did you?
- Yes.

489
00:42:44,238 --> 00:42:46,146
- Why else?
- Oh my.

490
00:42:46,147 --> 00:42:48,764
I was kidding.

491
00:42:48,788 --> 00:42:50,517
It took me seven years
to become a college student.

492
00:42:50,518 --> 00:42:52,186
I'm just loving it.

493
00:42:52,187 --> 00:42:55,007
I want to try everything
I haven't done before.

494
00:42:55,008 --> 00:42:57,658
So please don't be mad, Bong Pal.

495
00:43:01,308 --> 00:43:03,788
Bong Pal. Bong Bong.

496
00:43:05,928 --> 00:43:08,258
Bong Pal, please...

497
00:43:12,948 --> 00:43:15,546
